sql:
SELECT officer_name, badge_number, rank 
FROM reporting_officers 
WHERE police_station_id = 0;

SELECT district_name
FROM districts
WHERE district_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "neighborhoods" refers to 'districts';
- "received the most comments" means 'having the highest feedback count';
- 'reported incidents' refers to 'crimes'.

Fresh and legitimate crimes: These refer to crimes marked as new and not unfounded, without any administrative adjustments;
Main Street: Part of the full address includes "Main St";
Boundaries: The geographical coordinates indicate the range;
Currently under investigation: Refers to 'Open' status reports;
Reported more than twice on average: Average count of occurrences per crime type is greater than 2.

sql:
SELECT neighborhood_id
FROM neighborhoods
WHERE population > (SELECT AVG(population) FROM neighborhoods);

SELECT neighborhood_name
FROM neighborhoods
WHERE population > 10000;

SELECT feedback_text
FROM public_feedback
WHERE feedback_id = 1;
